notes_display: In Historical Sketches of the Paper Currency of the American Colonies by Henry Phillips, Jr. (1865). Given to Dr. Jesse C. Green in 1890. Leaf 56I.
issue_place_s: Philadelphia, Pennsylvania, United States of America
issue_obverse_legend_s: TWENTY SHILLINGS. THIS BILL shall pass current for TWENTY SHILLINGS wiin the Province of Pensylvania, according to an Act of General Assembly of the said Province, made in the 30th Year of the Reign of KING GEORGE II. Dated Oct. 1, 1756. Twenty Shillings.
issue_reverse_legend_s: TWENTY SHILL. | To Counterfeit is DEATH | Printed by B. Franklin, and D. HALL. 1756.
